where qi and qj are the partial charges, and si and sj are the ionic radius of the ith and jth species, respectively. Aij and Cij are respectively the overlap repulsive energy and dispersion energy between the ith and jth ions. Listed in Table 1 are the potential parameters employed taken from a previous study by Kumar and Yashonath.49,50
The initial structures of the NASICONs are taken from the X-ray study of Boilot et al.51 The simulation box is made from 3 Â 3 Â 1 unit cells having rhomohedral (R3%C) symmetry. The simulation super-cell thus includes a total of 972 ions (54-Na, 108-Zr, 162-P and 648-O) for NaZr2(PO4)3 and 1134 ions (216-Na, 108-Zr, 162-P and 648-O) for Na4Zr2(SiO4)3. The initial X-ray structures51 of both systems are relaxed using the isothermal–isobaric (NPT) ensemble at 500 K. The dimensions of the relaxed simulation box are a = b = 26.989 Å, c = 22.672 Å for NaZr2(PO4)3 and a = b = 27.680 Å, c = 22.379 Å for Na4Zr2(SiO4)3. At an integration time-step of 2 fs, the production run for NaZr2(PO4)3 was 100 ns long, while that for Na4Zr2(SiO4)3 was 200 ns long for better convergence of properties.
